<br>
In this country, in this world... it is not illegal to be biased against stupid people.  The largest thing we as a people judge other people on, is how they talk(or in this forum, type).  It is basically the first interaction we have with someone aside from simply seeing their name or face on the street.<br>
<br>
So you want to complain out certain things, like us not being racist, sexist... whatever... sorry bud, it's perfectly alright to not light morons.  Ever go to a job interview?  Did you sound like a tool?  Maybe you actually tried to speak clearly, tried to use good diction?  You see, in the realy world, the business world, this is how things go.  By and large, I would estimate that most of the people who play EQ and frequent this board, teens/high schoolers making up the other chunk, are professional people.  These people have real lives, have real jobs, and in most instances... they have to use their abilities to communicate with others to the best of their ability, because it means their job.  That is how the real world is.  Now if you work at a gas station and all you need to say is, &quot;that'll be a dolla fitty, hee yuh&quot; then you're doing all right. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=twompyeverblaze>Twompy Everblaze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Qeynos Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#628CBC>(7/16/03 9:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1039.topic&index=82>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Grammer snobs</span><hr size=1> Drack's skull is way too thick to understand the real point of the so-called &quot;grammar snobs&quot;. It is not the lack of literacy or proper grammer that causes frustration, but the lack of desire for self-improvement. Why is it so hard for you to understand the distinction?  <br>
